<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1912,2011]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1912,1939]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Anterior reclinate small (OR2/OR1 0.73, vs.&gt;.08–0.93); apex of male abdomen dark (including epandrium); distiphallus width in dorsoventral view at least twice that of phallus stem, large and thick in lateral view, with fine medial spicules, no medial scales; lateral margin of aedeagus not serrate, tip papillate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,152,179]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description:</emphasis>
Coloration typical of group, katepisternum and meron very slightly infuscate and pollinose; tergite 6 lighter than preceding segments, epandrium and cerci darker. Setation as in diagnosis and measurements. Protarsal spines with typical array of 8 fang-shaped spines alternating in size, 4 on each on two basal tarsomeres. Male genitalia: Hypandrium with narrowed anterior end, width 0.5x the posterior end; phallus in dorsoventral view gradually broadened subapically to at least twice the width of phallus shaft. Like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Jones" authorityYear="2020" box="[935,1102,298,323]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cameroonensis">
<emphasis box="[935,1102,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">cameroonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without coarse or fine scales, only minute pimpules apically, short, dense spicules medially; aedeagus best distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Jones" authorityYear="2020" box="[1240,1407,334,359]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cameroonensis">
<emphasis box="[1240,1407,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">cameroonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lateral view, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Jones" authorityYear="2020" box="[299,409,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freidbergi">
<emphasis box="[299,409,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">freidbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being larger and much thicker (
<figureCitation box="[778,877,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1868,1893]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,186,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[163,1425,181,1843]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, and postgonite for most species in the Drosophila spinipes group, lateral views, all to the same scale. Spicules on the phallus are on the inner (mesal) surface. A. D. suma Burla (HS-01). B. D. malagasy n. sp. (HS- 17). C. D. malagasy n. sp. (HS-20). D. D. malagasy n. sp. (HS-22). E. D. cameroonensis n. sp. (HS- 10). F. D. hypandrilata n. sp. (HS- 38). G. sp. D (HS- 03). H. D. freidbergi n. sp. (HS- 06). I. D. nigrospinipes n. sp. (HS-24). J. D. phalloserra n. sp. (HS-07). K. D. phalloserra n. sp. (HS-08). L. D. phalloserra n. sp. (DMSA 140413)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933824" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3933824/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 12h</figureCitation>
, cf. fig. 12e). Female unknown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1253,1428,369,395]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Measurements</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,224,405,431]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Head:</emphasis>
HD/HW 0.77; FL/LFW 0.89; VB2/VB1 0.64; EW/ED 0.67; OR2/OR1 0.73; OR3/OR1 1.06; OC/POC 1.50; FW/FD 0.68; ODB/ODA 0.40. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[499,597,441,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thorax:</emphasis>
ThL 
<quantity box="[655,760,441,467]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="0.99">0.99 mm</quantity>
.; UPS/LHS 0.82; LHS/ThL 0.23; ADC/PDC 0.46; AKE/PKE 0.63; LF1/LF2 0.84.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
